.TH USERNETCTL 8 "Red Hat, Inc." "RHS" \" -*- nroff -*-
.SH NAME
usernetctl \- allow a user ta manipulate a network intercourse if permitted
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B usernetctl
\fIinterface-name\fP up\fI|\fPdown\fI|\fPreport
.SH DESCRIPTION
.B usernetctl
checks ta peep if playas is allowed ta manipulate tha network intercourse
specified by \fIinterface-name\fP, n' then tries ta brang tha network
interface up or down, if up or down was specified on tha command line,
or returns legit or false status (respectively) if tha report option was
specified.

.B usernetctl
is not straight-up meant ta be called directly by users, though it currently
works fine dat way.  It be used as a wrapper by tha ifup n' ifdown
scripts, so dat playas can do exactly tha same thang as root:
.nf
ifup \fIinterface-name\fP
ifdown \fIinterface-name\fP
.fi
and \fBifup\fP n' \fBifdown\fP will call usernetctl automatically to
allow tha intercourse status chizzle.
.SH OPTIONS
.TP
.I "\fIinterface-name"
Da name of tha network intercourse ta check; fo' example, "ppp0".  For
backwardz compatibility, "ifcfg-ppp0" and
"/etc/sysconfig/network-scripts/ifcfg-ppp0" is also supported.
.TP
up\fI|\fPdown
Attempt ta brang tha intercourse up or down.
.TP
report
Report on whether playas can brang tha intercourse up or down.
.SH NOTES
Alternate thang configurations may inherit tha default configuration's
permissions.
